### [POST] Create a new employee with valid data (Success)
POST http://localhost:5000/v1/api/Employee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "EmployeeCode": "NV001",
  "Username": "johndoe",
  "Email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "Fullname": "John Doe",
  "Age": 30,
  "Address": "123 Main St",
  "DepartmentId": "3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6"
}

### [POST] Create a new employee with missing required fields (Failure: EmployeeCode is required)
POST http://localhost:80/v1/api/Employee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Username": "jane",
  "Email": "jane@example.com",
  "Fullname": "Jane",
  "Age": 25,
  "DepartmentId": "3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6"
}

### [POST] Create a new employee with invalid email format (Failure)
POST http://localhost:80/v1/api/Employee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "EmployeeCode": "NV002",
  "Username": "bob",
  "Email": "invalid-email",
  "Fullname": "Bob",
  "Age": 22,
  "DepartmentId": "3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6"
}

### [POST] Create a new employee with EmployeeCode over 20 chars (Failure)
POST http://localhost:80/v1/api/Employee
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "EmployeeCode": "NV00000000000000000001",
  "Username": "tester",
  "Email": "tester@example.com",
  "Fullname": "Tester",
  "Age": 20,
  "DepartmentId": "3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6"
}

